metadata.name: Altered #106
metadata.description:
Adj. Changed in character or composition, typically in a comparatively small but significant way.

Please note that the display is progressive and can take some time to finalize.

Artwork by Patrice Orenes-Lerma - @patxol - 2022
Made with math, love & p5js.
CC BY-SA 4.0 https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/

Features include :

- 20 color palettes (10 standard, 10 rare)
- 8 palette progression types
- 3 aspect ratio (Portrait is standard, 1:1 and landscape are rare)
- 8 Alteration types
- 3 Alteration power levels
- 5 types of symmetry
- 3 densities
- Spaced mode and Sharp mode

Enjoy the magic of northern lights over a serene lake at night.

May 2022 - de_Frahme

metadata.name: Stitched: Trauma #128
metadata.description:
"Every happy family is alike; every unhappy family is unhappy in its own way." -- Tolstoy

Stitched: trauma is based on the same code, and premise, as Stitched, with one twist: childhood trauma distorts experiences and events; some are wildly chaotic; others obsessively retrace a few curves. It is an experiment in combinatorial complexity: are two mints ever indistinguishable? 

The distortion has been carefully designed to allow a huge space of legibly distinct possibilities.

controls:

mouse click or space bar: pause / unpause / reset animation
s: save current frame
f: toggle between square format and stretch aspect ratio
1-6: set pixel density

attributes.name: Symmetry
attributes.value: Reflection in y, Reflection in x, Reflection across x+y=0

metadata.name: Distortion City Tool #284
metadata.description: This is the tool I created for Distortion City series. Click to draw the shape, toggle line and adjust the fxrand() (rnd and basement) to see how they distorted. Shift + click on the line to add points, shift + click on the point to delete the point. Save Json if you want to use in your program. This is not artwork but because all Distortion City Series stay at fxhash, I share here.

metadata.name: Paesaggio #150
metadata.description:
In this work I used the tools I learned in developing precedent works to generate a landscape with hills, flowers, streams, ruins, sky and clouds. The generated landscape gives the impression of a natural one but at the same time it has some "abstract" traits that reveal the geometrical properties of the noise generation process. This noise is used both for the morphological aspect and for colors assignment.

Developed with p5.js using WEBGL renderer.
Rendering is faster with chrome browser.

[s] to save a 1600x1600 png.


Features:
"Palette": 12 colormap
"Sky":  Day, Night, Gray - 15% Gray, 20% Night, 65% Day
"Ruins": True, False - 33% True
"Streams": True, False - 33% True
"Flower": Red-Blue, Fuchsia-Yellow, Rose-Violet
"Border": True, False - 25% True


Created by Andrea Belloni, fxhash: anbello, twitter: @Waterflowing0. Licensed under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0, see LICENSE.txt for more information.

metadata.name: Rêve em Nuvens #1
metadata.description:
Even though sometimes our horizon seems to be obscured by problems and difficulties, the weather is always clear above the clouds.

"Rêves em Nuvens", a mixture of French and Portuguese words meaning "Dreams in the clouds", is intended to be a message of hope and encouragement for all those who, at some point, have seen their perspectives disappear. They are still there, the stars and the sky are only hidden behind clouds.

Born from a two-month collaboration between Omar Lobato and Estienne, "Rêve em Nuvens" uses noise assemblages to reproduce a cloudy sky, sometimes at night under a full moon, during a late afternoon or a sunny day. 

The colors, shape, texture and turbulence of the clouds are all variations that will give this series a style that can be both realistic and fantastic.

Although the parameters are attached to the hash of each edition, certain options are offered in order to be able to generate the image in the style that suits you best, whether for display on screen, or for printing:

Press the [1] key to toggle the noise effect
Press the [2] key to toggle the stucco texture
Press the [3] key to toggle the lines texture

Press the [S] key to save a 4K image in PNG format

Add "?size=xxx" at the end of the url to generate an image of xxx pixels

Authors: Omar Lobato & Estienne
May 2022

metadata.name: Euphonic #246
metadata.description:
Euphonic is an exploration of the emergent visual properties that arise from placing layers of simple lines atop one another.

In general this effect is called the Moiré effect. This effect really feels best in the tactile - when you have a printed page and an acetate sheet. This piece attempts to recreate that tactile joy.

This is built in WebGL 2 and so doesn't work in Safari 14 and below. All latest browsers will work as expected.

Licensing: BY-NC-ND see license.md for details.

metadata.name: Little Trees #180
metadata.description:
Delicate, little trees. Some with green leaves, some with orange, some with red. This is the genesis project of Brian Gawlik.

The default resolution is 3600x3600. To redraw and save as an image at a different resolution - in the live view, open your browser's devtools and execute the function saveImg(pixWidth) where pixWidth is the desired width in pixels of the image. For example, saveImg(4096) will prompt you to download a 4096x4096 image. It is recommended not to export below 2400x2400 as this will compromise the aesthetic of the shadow.

metadata.name: Ethereal Microcosm #108
metadata.description:
An exploration of algorithmic organisms in a contained environment.

This piece is about the simulation of microscopic patterns using a high number of even tinier agents all following the same rules. Different species evolve and interact together, resulting in stabilizing patterns out of their parametric configurations. A form of artificial life.

This work is based on the paper "Characteristics of pattern formation and evolution in approximations of physarum transport networks", written by Jeff Jones and popularized in the artistic field by Sage Jenson. Some features were added to increase the visual and behavioral complexity of the system. Agents are divided into different species, with their own set of rules and interacting with their own substrate. Substrates also interact with each other and agents will mutate in contact of some of them.

NFT License
Runs properly on Chrome 97.0.4692.99
GPU intensive
